Auth

Authentication operations

Find more about authentication

Authenticate and generate JWT token

Authenticates a user with username and password, and returns a JWT token for API access.

This endpoint does not require authentication.

Note: This endpoint is available at /auth/login (not under /v1.0 prefix).

Request Body schema: application/json
required
username
required
string

The username (agent username or customer email)

password
required
string <password>

The user password

Responses

https://api.voipbin.net/v1.0/auth/login

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "username": "user@example.com",
  • "password": "********"
}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 400
  • 401
  • 429
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "username": "user@example.com",
  • "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
}

Request a password reset

Sends a password reset email to the agent's registered email address.

This endpoint always returns 200 regardless of whether the username exists, to prevent username enumeration.

This endpoint does not require authentication.

Note: This endpoint is available at /auth/password-forgot (not under /v1.0 prefix).

Request Body schema: application/json
required
username
required
string

The agent's username (email address)

Responses

https://api.voipbin.net/v1.0/auth/password-forgot

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "username": "user@example.com"
}

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json
{ }

Password reset page

Serves an HTML page with a password reset form.

The agent clicks the reset link from their email, which opens this page. The page contains a form to enter a new password.

This endpoint does not require authentication.

Note: This endpoint is available at /auth/password-reset (not under /v1.0 prefix).

query Parameters
token
required
string

The password reset token from the email link

Responses

https://api.voipbin.net/v1.0/auth/password-reset

Execute password reset

Validates the reset token and updates the agent's password.

This endpoint does not require authentication.

Note: This endpoint is available at /auth/password-reset (not under /v1.0 prefix).

Request Body schema: application/json
required
token
required
string

The password reset token from the email link

password
required
string <password> >= 8 characters

The new password

Responses

https://api.voipbin.net/v1.0/auth/password-reset

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "token": "string",
  • "password": "pa$$word"
}

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json
{ }

Create a new talk chat

Creates a new talk chat and returns the created talk's details.

Participant requirements by type:

  • direct: Requires exactly 1 other participant (creator is automatically added as second participant)
  • group: Can start with 0 or more participants (creator is automatically added, members can be added/removed later)
  • talk: No additional participants required (creator is automatically added)

Note: If the creator includes themselves in the participants list, they will not be added twice.

Request Body schema: application/json
type
required
string (TalkManagerTalkType)
Enum: "direct" "group" "talk"

Type of the talk.

name
string

Talk name (optional).

detail
string

Talk description/detail (optional).

Array of objects (TalkManagerParticipantInput)

List of participants to add to the chat (creator is added automatically).
